57.3	Jerusalem_syndrome	Jerusalem syndrome	The Jerusalem syndrome is a group of mental phenomena involving the presence of either religiously themed obsessive ideas, delusions or other psychosis-like experiences that are triggered by a visit to the city of Jerusalem. It is not endemic to one single religion or denomination but has affected Jews, Christians and Muslims of many different backgrounds.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a9/Jerusalem_Dominus_flevit_BW_1.JPG/230px-Jerusalem_Dominus_flevit_BW_1.JPG
